reviewText:
In a sarcastic comic form of a self-mutilations Australian movies famous for, a story of a first New South Wells general-governor William Bligh and his British colonists-founders of Sydney ostracises the Australia of the time the play was created, leaving none but much later topic on same gender marriage outside a spotlight.

What is the most funny, two DVD thirteen episodes ended with no end of story while reality is up to date similar to 1800s depicted.

Highly recommended for interesting in international affairs, human rights etc.
